cruise_purpose:
The objectives of both legs are to: 
1)        Collect data needed to estimate the distribution and abundance of marine mammals, sea turtles and seabirds; 
2)        Collect vocalizations of cetaceans using passive acoustic hydrophones;
3)        Collect data needed to estimate the distribution and relative abundance of plankton using nets with CTDs, visual plankton recorder, and the EK-60; 
4)        Collect hydrographic and meteorological data, and 
5)        When possible, collect biopsy samples and photo-identification pictures of cetaceans.

